Organ trafficking in Russia has been a growing concern, with doctors accused of illegal kidney removal.
A new law allows local hospitals to perform organ transplants, previously limited to larger facilities.
Reports from Canada highlight organ transplant scandals in China involving military hospitals.
In the Philippines, organ donation is a lucrative business, especially among the poor.
In the US, efforts are being made to expand incompatible heart transplants for infants.
Legal and ethical concerns arise regarding incentivizing organ donation for inmates.
Additionally, Zimbabwe and China are working on reviving and regulating their organ donation programs to meet global health standards.
